transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, Joanna speaking, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I ordered some product from you the other day and I just tried to do something and it

Speaker 1: wanted my e-mail address and I put it in there and it wouldn't accept it.

Speaker 2: So I went back to the original order and I discovered somehow I had overlooked the fact

Speaker 1: that you had put my old e-mail address in there and that's no longer valid.

Speaker 2: I need to change that.

Speaker 1: Okay, Mr. Stakely, I have your account pulled up.

Speaker 2: Can you just verify your date of birth and I'll update your e-mail address?

Speaker 1: Yes, October 20, 1936.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you, sir.

Speaker 1: Now, I can go ahead and update your e-mail.

Speaker 2: It says davidstakelyattampabay.rr.com.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's the old one.

Speaker 2: That's no good anymore.

Speaker 1: Okay, what do you want me to update it to?

Speaker 2: Margaretanddavidatgmail.com.

Speaker 1: That's M-A-R-G-I-T, letter N, david, at gmail.com.

Speaker 2: Okay, so let me repeat that.

Speaker 1: So Margaret, I think I have all of it except for Margaret.

Speaker 2: I just want to make sure I got the spelling right.

Speaker 1: M-A-R-G-I-T?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, and then N and then David?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, I've gone ahead and updated that for you, sir, so you should be able to log on now.

Speaker 2: Yes, okay, good.

Speaker 1: Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: My pleasure.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
